						<p>This record is engraved in continuation of No. 333. On the <hi rend="bold">10th day of Āśvayuja</hi> of the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Vijaya</hi> (= probably A.D. 1233-34) <hi rend="italic">Mahāvaḍḍavyavahāri</hi> <hi rend="bold">Vāsudēva-Nāyaka</hi> is said to have made a gift of 2 <hi rend="italic">gadyāṇas</hi> for making a flower garden for the service of the god Gōpāladēva.</p>						

